--- body ---
## Context

Split from 0276 (RDJ-26561 R&R, tracker 0274, remark R1-12): the referee asks
how many duplicates each procedure removes — (1) DOI-based, (2) title+year
matching. This ticket produces the *numbers* as a traceable artifact; 0276
writes the prose that cites them. Split because obtaining the counts may
touch Phase-1 instrumentation (padme, API-dependent, author-coordinated)
while the prose is an ordinary manuscript PR.

## Relevant files

- Phase-1 dedup implementation in `scripts/` (locate the actual dedup step)
- `data/catalogs/run_reports/` — counts may already exist there; check first
- `scripts/schemas.py` — schema if a new CSV artifact is added

## Actions

1. Check existing run reports for per-procedure dedup counts.
2. If absent, instrument the dedup step to log/emit them (per-procedure
   breakdown), coordinating any Phase-1 rerun with the author — never
   triggered from the manuscript build (phase separation).
3. Land the counts as an archived artifact the paper can cite (run report or
   small derived table with a Make target).

## Test

- The artifact regenerates deterministically given the same inputs; counts
  sum consistently with total duplicates removed.

## Verification

- [ ] Counts artifact archived and referenced by path

## Invariants

- Phase separation; no hand-curated numbers.

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Per-procedure dedup counts exist as a pipeline-traceable artifact
- [ ] 0276 unblocked with the artifact path recorded in its body or log

## Plan (raid 2026-07-22, Imagine findings)

Dedup lives in `scripts/harvest/catalog_merge.py` (Phase-1 corpus-discover):
DOI pass at lines ~188-196, title+year pass at ~198-202 via
`_dedup_no_doi_records()`. Counts currently go only to `log.info` — never
persisted; no `catalog_merge__*.json` exists in `data/catalogs/run_reports/`.

Simplest path — no padme, no API, no author-coordinated rerun: the stage's
dvc.yaml deps are the six already-archived per-source catalog CSVs (all local).

1. Instrument `catalog_merge.py` with a flat `counters` dict (records before
   dedup, with/without DOI split, doi_duplicates_removed,
   title_year_duplicates_removed, dropped_empty_title, final total) and call
   `save_run_report(counters, run_id, script_name)` per the `corpus_align.py`
   pattern (`pipeline_io.py:142-169`). No new CSV, no Pandera schema, no new
   Make target — the JSON run-report convention is the house artifact shape
   (a new CSV+schema here would be premature abstraction).
2. Rerun only this stage offline: `make corpus-discover` (wraps
   `dvc repro catalog_merge`; never bare `dvc repro`).
3. Byte-compare new `unified_works.csv` against the archived one — dedup
   logic must be unchanged, only reporting added.
4. Commit `run_reports/catalog_merge__*.json` + `run_reports.dvc` pointer +
   `dvc.lock` stage-hash bump; record the artifact path in 0276's log.

First test (red): unit test on a small synthetic frame through the dedup
helpers asserting the counters sum: rows_in - doi_removed - title_year_removed
- dropped_empty_title == rows_out, and that the run report carries the
per-procedure keys.
